# Frontend Design Patterns Rules

## 1. Container / Presentational Pattern

- Container components manage state and logic
- Presentational components handle UI only
- Do not mix concerns unless component is trivial

---

## 2. Custom Hooks Pattern

- Shared logic must be extracted into hooks
- Hooks must not render UI
- Hooks must encapsulate reusable behavior and side effects

---

## 3. Adapter Pattern

- All external API data must be normalized via adapters
- UI must never depend on raw API response structure
- Data transformation must occur before UI layer

---

## 4. Compound Components Pattern

- Use compound components for complex UI systems
- Components must remain composable and flexible
- Avoid excessive prop drilling

---

## 5. Composition Over Inheritance

- Prefer composition for reuse and extension
- Avoid inheritance-based UI design patterns

---

## 6. Pattern Selection Rule

- Patterns must only be used when complexity justifies them
- Do NOT introduce patterns prematurely
- Prefer simplicity over abstraction unless needed